One of the most entertaining things in the world to me is to act dumb or naïve when I know someone is lying. Sometimes it’s merely for my own laugh and sometimes it’s to “keep the peace” in survival. When you have a highly intuitive nature, unfortunately you always know the truth. Since I was a little girl, I never wanted “the gifts”. Remember at age eight, I could look at someone’s face or listen to their voice and tell what they were thinking along with their whole life story…. Each one of us have so many gifts and are powerful beyond measure. Society doesn’t encourage such things and wants us to fit into their mold. 
Man-made religion teaches us to condemn ourselves if we do anything against a god/energy/source that created us… pretty silly and extremely small minded. There’s so much control on this planet, that we are rarely free to express who we truly are. Everything that I’ve done thus far in this life is to set out to bridge the gaps of color, creed, culture, sexual preference, sexual identity, religions or walks of life….We are ALL one. We are ALL the same. We are ALL love. The divisions come from the conditioning of society, environment etc. 

We are feeling and seeing so many shifts in the world right now… one of the most beautiful things, is people having more courage to truly embrace who they are in truth. The greatest desire of my heart is that each of us feel liberated from the bonds that hold us back from expressing the essence of who we were created to be. 

We cannot change what we are unwilling to confront.

#DrZoe 👑
